steps.instruction:
Made by Christina Chaey and can be found [here](https://www.bonappetit.com/recipe/spicy-chicken-lettuce-wraps)

### Prep
- Thinly slice *only* the white and pale green parts of the scallion. 

### Steps
1. Mix soy sauce, brown sugar, fish sauce, and 1 Tbsp. sambal oelek in a small bowl; set aside.
2. Heat oil in a skillet over medium
3. Add scallions and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened (a little color is okay), about 3 minutes
4. Add chicken and lightly season with salt. Cook, breaking up with a wooden spoon and tossing occasionally, until chicken is cooked through, 57 minutes
5. Add reserved soy sauce mixture and cook, tossing occasionally, until liquid is almost completely reduced, about 2 minutes.
6. Serve chicken mixture with lettuce, herbs, lime wedges, and more sambal oelek for making lettuce wraps.

ingredients.note: Or Sriracha, plus more for serving
White and pale green parts only
